We were just discussing possible dishes to get and she wrote down everything we said even though we haven't actually ordered it. We didn't realize this until the food was brought out. We didn't want to argue with her so ended up paying for everything.

We also thought we ordered too much and just wanted to ask if we could take a dish off the order. She started yelling at us when we were only asking if it was possible. Extremely bad attitude and very obnoxious.

The food here is also not that great. A lot of the dishes we ordered was pretty flavorless. And I'm talking about their "authentic" dishes, not their Americanized ones. Their salt and pepper squid was good, though it's hard to mess that up. Can definitely get better authentic Chinese food elsewhere.

They also cater for large parties in their upstairs dining area. Do not do this. They overcharge for parties by serving subpar food and charge a certain price per person.

text:
We go to Fancy Nails about every 6 weeks. The Shellac manicures (~$35) are a good price for the area and the selection of colors is crazy. They have more colors than any other place I've been.

The pedicures (~$35) are really good for the price too and the staff are all really friendly. They are attentive and do a good job with the cuticles. They will even wrap your toes if they aren't wuite dry so you can put on your shoes if you didn't bring sandals.

Fancy Nails is also willing to fix pedis/manis that chip shortly after, which I will say doesn't normally happen, but every once in a while. They also don't make a stink when i make a reservation and show up a bit late because of traffic or weather.

They sell gift certificates and are open earlier, at 9, during the holidays.

I think I'm giving this place a 4 becuase I don't love the chairs they have for the pedis and they have one woman who was very rude to a friend of mine. They fixed that right up though.

text:
OK, after all the buzz of this place, I finally made my way in there. Let's be honest, back in the day there was a 3 hour waiting line. I only would wait for 3 hours in the ER if I'm bleeding more than half gallon per hour, but never for food and furthermore never for pizza.

So now that things have settled a little bit, it was my time to visit the place. In my crew there were 4 kids although the place is far from kid friendly, and so is the service. Anyhow, let's cut to the chase.

The menu, although small, has a good selection. The antipasto was good with one meat, one cheese, some cauliflower, red pepper, olives and a couple of other things. It was good and a nice portion.

I also had the caprese salad but I really missed some balsamic vinegar. The EVOO was tasteful but some balsamic is a must (in my opinion).

I also had the rosa pizza. The parmesano raggiano flavor dominates in a super pleasent way. I would recommend people to share because the whole thing (with the same flavor) is a little too much. Don't take me wrong, I loved this pizza but maybe would like to taste something else as well.

They don't have deserts besides a biscotte that was good and I had a double capuccino that was good as well.

One thing I didn't like is that they don't have lemonade. WTH? I was craving an Arnold Palmer to fight the heat back but had to settle with an ice tea.

Anyways, great food, the place worth it if you don't have to wait, nice ambiance and the neighborhood is nice for a walk after the feast.

I might go back some day soon to try other pizzas.
label: neutral

text: Barbant, inintéressant, prétentieux et mal joué. Voilà à peu près tout ce que je pense de ce film. Une catastrophe ambulante, à croire que ce Dolan s'est dit qu'en empruntant les thèmes ambigus du cinéma d'Honoré, l'estéthique des ralentis de Wong kar Wai dans In the mood for love, la lenteur de Somewhere de Coppola, et en y rajoutant un peu de Bang bang Dalidesque pour faire classe, il allait nous pondre un truc original. Pour moi c'est une parfaite horreur, cruellement creuse. C'est horriblement bobo, faussement décadent, affreusement surjoué par des acteurs horripilants (et là on peut me dire que toutes leurs mimiques exorbitantes sont voulues et font partie du charme du film, même si elles sont introduites ici avec second degré elles m'ont quand même affreusement tapé sur le système), et vide. Il faudra que l'on m'explique ce que ce Dolan a d'un prodige du cinéma ! Le seul petit point positif que je peux lui trouver, c'est qu'il y a tout de même parfois de jolies images.
label: negative

text:
Been here a few times, the most recent of which was Wednesday evening for their annual crawfish broil (offered Wednesdays and Thursdays through March and April). The seafood here is pretty fresh and service is usually top-notch. 

I'm not a fan of crawfish, but my friends always rave about it, so I gave it a shot. I played it safe and ordered the 1 1/4 lb option ($7.95) while they ordered 2.5 lbs ($15.90). I ate about four of the crawfish and sorry folks, still not a fan. The seasoning was too spicy and salty. I ate the corn and gave the rest of the crawfish away. I'll stick to crab, lobster or shrimp - more meat.

I ordered the jumbo lump crab cake ($13.95) and shared an order of the P.E.I. mussels ($10.95). The crab cake was delicious - kudos to them for not skimping on the meat. I was not a fan of mussels before Pappadeaux, but now I'm hooked and always order their P.E.I. mussels. 

This place seems to always be packed, regardless of which day of the week it is.
label: negative

text:
I LOVED THIS HOTEL!!!!
First off, this review may be slanted as I'm typically a Best Western value type chick who doesn't enjoy spending $5 for a Vitamin water in the mini bar, though I love having access to one knowing it's there if I need it. Anyway, the reason I selected this upscale boutique hotel is ... my husband was off to Boston with one purpose - Extreme Beer Fest. He was to be involved with his buddies and festival the ENTIRE weekend leaving me to explore alone, etc. I selected this hotel as it was closest to the Cyclarama (sp?) and right outside a t-stop and seemed very safe, upscale without being a stuffy Marriott, youthful and COMFY .
Safe/Secure & Helpful!
The staff will bend over backwards for you. I locked myself out of the room and waited an entire 60 seconds for someone to help me get back in - they even checked my ID to make sure I wasn't breaking into a room - though I was in my socks and PJs.
The concierge is busy, but makes time for you and acknowledges you even when they’re on a call or with another customer making you feel important. With a few moments notice, they gave my husband a ride to his walk-able destination (it was bitter cold that weekend!) in their new Smart cars – super cute cars by the way! I believe they will drive one person within 1 mile of the hotel. Smart cars only have room for one person along with the driver, so couples, this won’t help you, in my case it worked out fine.
Every night when my husband returned late in the evening, they checked his ID and room key to make sure he was really staying at the hotel. This was very comforting to me as a woman spending most of my time alone at the hotel. Also, ladies, the doors have THREE locks on them.
Room Service
Though slightly overpriced with a $4 service charge and automatic 18% gratuity added, the food was great (I ordered a chicken salad on roll with fries – mmm!)
The food arrived quickly and prepared perfectly and correctly.
Perks & Package Deals
Please make sure you sign up for the iPrefer card which allows you use of the Internet for free and late/early check ins/outs. The person who took my reservation was shockingly helpful having the consumer’s best interest in mind – he suggested it, knowing times are tough I’m sure. They have great packages, the one we took advantage of was based on the temperature outside. We paid $30 for Friday night’s stay and $295 for Saturday. Our package also included free hot cocoa and parking and a 2-hour tour of Boston via a TROLLEY ride! I loved it! My biggest regret was not doing the haunted/ghost tour the evening before! I loved the room, decorated so much in my style, my husband kept teasing me. Very hip, modern – though make sure everything works – three of our four reading lights were burnt out but I didn’t bother to report it. The upscale bathroom toiletries are amazing and if you’re there more than one night, they will restock them!
Location
Perfectly situated by the Prudential Center, Barnes & Noble, PF Chang’s, Daily Grill, Cheesecake Factory, an oversized Shaw’s supermarket (get your bottled water, snacks there, $1 DVDs for the kids and save $ on the overpriced mini bar and in-room movies). Also a few blocks from Newbury Street – great shopping and galleries!
Restaurant
The French restaurant was great for breakfast, they give you a 15% off coupon – you may want to try walking a few feet to Thornton’s, we were feeling lazy and anxious to head home so we hit the brasserie for breakfast on Sunday morning on our way out.
Parking
Car is safe, only people for the hotel park there. We even saw an attendant keeping an eye on things – very reassuring! Parking was paid for by the hotel, thanks to our package!
label: positive

text: Went to club 12/13/14 a Sunday night when Brad Garrett headlined with Michael Malone and a Cowboy comedian from TX ( can't recall name) Club is small with tight seating at tiny round two-seater tables. Full bar with wine, beer and mixed drink options. No minimum. 3 pricing options with most expensive seats in first 7 rows. I sat in second section with good stage visibility. Go early because it's not reserved seating. Ushers will seat you according to your category purchased. Only snacks sold are $10/bag caramel or cheddar popcorn, not freshly popped and very small for price. Eat before you go. Be forewarned - Garrett is NOT politically correct and is very adult content but he is hilarious and plays the audience very well as did the other billed comics. I say definite go as long as you are not easily offended by ethnic jokes and overt sexual content. After the show all three comics remain in the lobby for meet/greet/photo ops. Garrett bought a round of drinks for a couple married 42 yrs and distributed logo hats to those he picked on during his set at the end of the show. Very nice gesture.
label: positive

text:
I must have gone to a very different restaurant than reviewers like 'Donald S'. Average beer selection? In addition to the standards, they had Left Hand Milk Stout and Stella on tap. 

Aesthetically, the place is pretty nice. Lots of TVs everywhere and the place is tall enough that I don't feel drowned out by music/broadcasters like I do at some other sports bars.

The service was pretty decent. Both times I came they kept my drinks topped off and stopped by often enough. They knew the menu well, which was good because there were enough choices to where I had to ask questions. The appetizers unfortunately took a while to come out, and I had just barely finished them when the entree came out. 

The food quality was great and surprised me. The Cajun Chicken sandwich was very good, though I thought it could have been spicier. They have different hamburger buns from the norm and I thought they tasted much better. The portions were very generous, I couldn't even finish my fries.
label: positive

text:
It was a sad walk from the Cosmo to here since it was our last day on our trip. It ended up being the best breakfast as well. 

Came in on Thursday morning around 10AM without a reservation. The hostess greeted us and asked if we wanted to wait for an outside patio table or dine in. We didn't have extra time to spare so we opted to dine inside. The wait was only a few minutes and we were led to a quint table that is inside the restaurant but also can be considered outside since it was next to the huge open area that had a nice breeze and view of the strip. 

After looking over their large brunch menu I ordered the fruit basket and the turkey and egg white omelette. The fruit basket was half of a cantaloupe cut to look like a flower with mango, pineapple, strawberries, grapes and berries inside. It was almost too pretty to eat. It also came with brown sugar, yogurt and a clear sweet syrup on the side. The fruit was all fresh sweet and ripe. The omelette was a nice size portion with tomatoes and avocado ontop. It was a little bland but the hot sauce I asked for spiced it up. I am not a hash browns fan but theirs are very good with grilled onions through out. 

Service was okay. Our waitress wasn't the warm and inviting type but got the job done. We did have a couple of times that we had to wait for the coffee and water to be refilled. 

The decor and layout reminded us of the cafes we had dined at when we were in Europe so Mon Ami Gabi did that correct. 

Prices is great for the quantity and quality of the food. Too bad we didn't dine here sooner otherwise we wouldnt have wasted our time nor money on the other two restaurants. But I will remember this restaurant for our next trip. For the fruit, two entrees, coffee, tax and tip the total came out around $52.00. 

Misc. info: reservations can only be made for inside the restaurant. The outside patio seating is first come first served.
label: neutral

text:
3.5 stars for food, 4 stars if the fountains were on when I came. 

FOOD
Complimentary bread and dip (4 stars): The bread variety was great. The spreads are all olive spreads, really good if you're an olive fan, if not, you're out of luck. 

Margarita Chicken Sandwich (3.5 stars): Juicy chicken, not amazing flavors but pretty good. Needed more basil. 

Spicy Chicken Flat bread (3.5 stars): Needed more flavor too, but still good. Not as crunchy on the bottom of the pizza, but the crust was crunchy. 

Cookie Sandwich Sundae (3.5 stars): Actually pretty small compared to the picture they show you! But good when it's so hot out outside! We asked to do both vanilla ice cream sandwiches and they did it. Good ice cream, good cookie. 

Complimentary Cream Puffs for special occasions: So nice they gave something for a special occasion. Who ever they have writing in chocolate is so talented, looked perfect. 

VIEW (4 stars):
With the fountains on it would definitely be a 5 star experience! We came on a weekday at 12:30PM for lunch and got a seat outside. I was waiting for the fountains until the waitress told me they don't turn on till 3PM on weekdays. WHATTTT, why am I here? Well it was still pretty to sit outside near the water and see the view of the strip, but the reason I came here was for those damn fountains, a little disappointing. So come after 3PM on weekdays! 

SERVICE (4 stars):
At first when they took us outside on the patio for seating they had 2 tables open, one with partial shade, the other in the over 100 degree heat. They need to fix the umbrellas to cover all the tables more, how can you eat in that heat! We ended up scrunching into the partial shaded table. But everyone was nice. Our waters were always filled, the waitress was a little chatty with certain tables so you had to wait till she was done to ask for stuff, but other than that everything was good.
label: negative

text:
Okay so I am not going to use some fancy intro or some catchy first few sentences to draw you in. This is a park, and being from Northern California there are many many parks and they are normally pretty nice. Now, don't get me wrong I think that every park has one or two creepers that you try to stay away from when you are there but for some reason this park had no shortage of those the night I was there.

Let me put that into perspective real quick. I was there for a kids softball game and nothing else. I know some of you may have had a bad image when I mentioned being in a park at night. walking into the park was interesting as they have it picnic areas and some of them happened to be occupied with large groups that seemed to be like something out of a movie. But the kicker was the smurf blue van with no windows except the one that looked like it was cut out of the side of the van. When I walked by I noticed that a few people were sitting in the back and when kids or groups of people walked by they would honk a bicycle horn out the window which was puzzling to me until I watched what was going on and it looked like they had been selling food out of the van. 

I'm all for food trucks, but not Guadalupe's unmarked food van. In a sense it reminded me of my time spent living in LA and venturing out into Santa Monica and Long Beach at night. 

The park itself seems okay for sports but I don't know that I would plan any family reunions or anything out there.
label: negative

text: I booked a king room at the Omni for my dad and his lady friend when they came to Indy for Father's Day weekend. When I saw the room, I was so jealous! The renovation of this hotel is outstanding. The high-end finishes, carpets, robes, furniture, accessories and bedding were extremely nice. This is a top-notch remodel, making this hotel on par with the new JW Marriott...maybe better, since this hotel is smaller and quieter. The room was huge and the bathroom was also a good size. I purchased the Circle Center Shopping package which included a gift card, outstanding brunch buffet at Severin Bar and Grill and valet parking...an outstanding value. Also, if you register for a frequent guest membership (which we did), morning coffee service (delivered to your door) and Internet are complimentary. The service was great. The staff was truly friendly and very helpful. Needless to say, Father's Day went great! I personally will stay there the next time I'm in Indy and would recommend it to friends or if you have family coming in from out of town.
label: positive

text: L’actrice Deborah François est Hélène Jegado, alias Fleur de Tonnerre. Cette bretonne fût considérée comme la plus grande tueuse en série de l’Histoire de France. En effet, avant d’avoir été guillotinée à Rennes en 1852, la paysanne empoisonna des dizaines de personnes. Sur le papier, nous étions déjà moyennement convaincus, mais sur l’écran c’est pire. Stéphanie Pillonca-Kervern signe une œuvre indigeste et trop bavarde dans une mise en scène floue et sinistre. On pardonnerait à quiconque souhaite quitter la salle tellement le rythme est excessivement fade. Fleur de Tonnerre ressemble à un vulgaire téléfilm français réalisé dans les années 70, avec en plus, un Benjamin Biolay inexpressif. D'autres critiques sur notre page Facebook : Cinéphiles 44
label: negative

text: What we have here is a film about how the pursuit of money & revenge can corrupt your soul... or something like that. Guy Ritchie, a director known for his reworking of the gangster genre, bites off more than he can chew with this one.His use of modern film noir to tackle the theme of a man setting himself free by swallowing his pride, being nice to his enemy & giving away all his money falls flat on it's face. When Jason Statham's character no longer fears Ray Liotta, it apparently drives Liotta crazy enough to blow his head off in the final scene. Why? Basically you cannot set up a mafiosi like the Liotta character, who has presumably got to his station in life by displaying the kind of ruthless behaviour evident throughout the film, only then to have him driven to suicide by nothing more than a pitying smile on the face of Statham's character.Before anyone starts to say I'm missing the point... I'm not. I get it OK? Opt out of the quest for riches & you'll find true happiness and inner peace. Be nice to your enemy and this will confuse him into self-destruction. This seems to be the gist of the movie and in itself this is not a bad premise for a story, although hardly original. The problem is that Ritchie simply doesn't have the skill as a movie maker to carry it off. At the moment when even Guy Ritchie realises this, he appears to get bored with the story and begins to insert red-herrings: The scene when Statham gets knocked over by a car - Why? The shooting of some scenes as Marvel comic animations... again, why?There are so many loose threads & unanswered questions left at the end of the movie you could get all 2001-ish about it and try figuring them out, or simply accept that there are no answers & each viewer will interpret things in their own way. Myself? I was so bored with the pompous tone of the film that I simply didn't care. Frankly the ending couldn't come too soon so that I didn't have to sit through any more of this pretentious psychobabble.A waste of two hours of my life.
label: negative

text: Copenhagen to Entebbe via Brussels, our trip with them was amazing. At the check-in counter the staff was so incredibly kind to put priority labels on all our of bags, even though only one in our group of four was entitled to it. A member in our group was in the need of wheel chair service and the staff was kind, attentive and service minded. Our group was transported from gate to gate with a smile. On the flight a member of our group could not eat the food they served, because it contained tomatoes and she’s allergic. We did not inform Brussels Airlines about this prior to our trip, so they had no way of being prepared for this. However, alternative food was presented by friendly and service minded staff. All in all we are super happy that we chose Brussels Airlines and will definitely do it again!
label: positive

I don't recommend ordering sashimi or sushi here as the quality of the fish is mediocre. My husband enjoyed their simple salmon, spicy tuna, and spicy scallop rolls. Yellowtail sashimi was not good.

Also tried the shishito peppers and garlic tofu which were good. Last was the okinawan soba-- noodles itself was great but the broth and pork belly (kind of tough) and extremely bland. 

I honestly think if they increased the quality of the produce and corrected the seasonings, they will have more business since their service is fantastic.

text:
The grand opening was yesterday and we were there tonight! 

My son got a $5.00 Large 1 topping pizza. He said it was good and ended up eating 1/2 of a large pizza!

I did the Provolone Cheese steak. Very good! Filled with lots of meat, peppers, onions, and Mayo! The bread wasn't soggy even though it was a little messy. I do think the peppers could be cooked a little more, they were crunchy and I don't like them like that. I will retry on the next visit.

Hubby got a steak, cheese, and mushroom. He said it was very good. He got the Onion rings and was disappointed. They were greasy and not as good as the one in Tempe. 

We also got an order or cheese bread and it was awesome.

The can probably hold about 25 inside and they have tables outside which is where we sat since the weather was so nice.

Over all I wish them the best of luck and plan to go back again.

text:
癖が凄い・・・
初めてハイレゾ対応イヤホンを購入したので、 これがハイレゾの音かどうかは判りませんが音はいいと思います。 イヤーチップもL.M.Sのサイズが付属してあるので装着感は良好でしたね。 ただひとつだけ気になったのがケーブルの癖ですね。 梱包の関係上ケーブルが纏められる訳ですが、紐解いても形が維持されるほど癖が強いです。 長く使えばケーブルの癖が解消されるかどうか判りませんが、 そこを気にしないのであれば、2000円前後の値段的にも十分オススメ出来る商品だと思います。 4月5日-追記：前日にレビューを書きましたが、 4月4日の午前中に届いてすぐ使い始めてその日の夜にイヤホンの右側が聞こえなくなりました。 何かに引っ掛かったり、ぐるぐる巻きにするような無理な使用はしていないですし、何が原因かもさっぱりでした。 音は良かったので早々に使い物にならなくなったのは残念です。 ハズレを引いたのかもしれませんが、今回の結果を見て☆4→☆2になります。 本当、音は良かったのになぁ・・・。

text:
It's not bad. But it's not great. It's more or less ok. The food is generally tasty, but considering the price I think it should be a smidge better. Also, the service was kind of lame. We had to flag down waiters just to get refills on our iced tea. We didn't get butter until we were halfway through with our meal. 

The corn on the cob was overcooked and the other side dishes were uninspired. The cornbread might have been the best part of the meal. My husband got the brisket, and he didn't seem to have any trouble eating it all. My pulled pork was palatable. But all of the meat was served on top of a giant piece of Texas toast. I think this was to give the appearance that we were getting more food. Given the price of our meals, I was hoping to have enough leftovers for another full meal. Alas, that wasn't the case.

The most annoying part of our experience was the lighting. The lamp above our table was outfitted with an amazingly bright light bulb. When I looked around the restaurant (after blinking at the spots in my eyes) I noticed that all of the people sitting in booths couldn't look across their table because the lights were so painful. The light was so bright that the bbq sauce on my pulled pork was making me squint from the glare. So, even if you are tempted by the booths, ask for a table. 

In short: if you're in the neighborhood and want meat, this will get the job done. Just remember to wear sunglasses inside.
label: negative

text:
Вводные тренировки. 
Тренировка по тренажерному залу. 
Девушка показала как работает дорожка, показала как работать с гантелями и разминка, в прошлом клубе мне проводили полноценную тренировку чтобы потом можно было заниматься самостоятельно и вообще понимать, что там нужно делать чтобы не покалечиться. 
На пробное занятие в бассейн вовсе не удалось попасть так как слишком плотная запись. 
Бассейн. 
В бассейне одна дорожка под детские секции, одна для спортивного плавания и остаётся 3. И на этих дорожках может оказаться по 5-6 человек 🤷‍♀️, ну все понимаем, что плыть в этом случае не удастся.
Так же видимо бассейн редко моют так как на стенах самого бассейна очень грязные полосы от воды. 
Далее групповые занятия, в основном они платные бесплатных совсем мало, то же самое с количеством мест во время занятия, тебе может просто не хватить места 😅
При стоимости абонемента в 30 000 хотелось бы все таки иметь возможность заниматься.

Решила вернуть абонемент и тут началось, оставь заявку через личный кабинет и жди 5 дней, через 5 дней позвони подтверди, жди еще 5 дней когда с тобой свяжутся из отдела возвратов. 
Операторы не отвечают на заданные вопросы, у них единственный ответ «ждите когда с вами свяжутся из отдела возвратов». 

Отдел возвратов работает 2 дня в неделю 🤷‍♀️
 
Для тех кто думает о покупке абонемента: лучше немного доплатить и пойти в другой зал, этот уже забит. 
У сотрудников сети фитнес клубов цель только одна это продать как можно больше абонементов, возникшие вопросы никто не поможет вам решить.
label: negative

text: Le monde rèel semble disparaitre dans cette oeuvre expèrimentale de Jess Franco entre fantasmes et rêveries! Le rèalisateur innove en quelque sorte, au point qu'il est difficile de savoir s'il s'agit là d'un rêve, d'une fuite dans un monde imaginaire, d'une vengeance où d'un deuil ? En fait, le spectateur comprend tout à la fin dans un dènouement à la "Planet of the Apes". C'est l'histoire d'un trompettiste qui va trouver une femme morte sur une plage et qui, mystèrieusement, va revenir à la vie! Jimmy est fou d'amour pour Wanda, à en perdre la raison, prêt à la poursuivre n'importe où, même en enfer si elle voulait! Jimmy court vers la mort qui, rapide, le rattrape et tous ses plaisirs au passè appartiennent! Dans une histoire particulièrement èclatèe, "Paroxismus" ne convainc qu'à moitiè! Abstraction faite des inconditionnels de Franco, espèce en voie disparition qui diront que ce mètrage est l'un de ses meilleurs! Sinon, petit rôle du sadique / soumis Klaus Kinski en playboy millionnaire et bande son des 60's psychè-pop très prèsente avec des images du Carnaval de Rio et d'Istanbul entre plage dèserte et mosquèe! « Venus in Furs va sourire. Venus in Furs va sourire. Venus in Furs va sourire »...

text: Rating: 4 stars - Loved ItHuge Thank You to CS Maxwell ~ Where's My Muse? blog for having King Cobra (Hot Rods #1) on her blog. Jayne Rylon has a new fan. I read a review that Eli and Alanso have a cameo in Hammer It Home (Powertools #6) and decided I would read the Powertools series in order before I read Eli and Alanso story in King Cobra. Nope now I will be reading King Cobra next as I am loving Jayne Rylon writing style and wow does she now how to write a scorching sex scene. Plus I do not think now I can read 5 more novels before.As for Kate's Crew I loved it with 5 sexy men and their power tools. Seriously crushing on Mike, a tattoo construction hero. There is no build up to their relationship since the story is a short novella but Jayne Rylon has a way of letting the readers know that Mike has been after Kate and she has been dodging him all summer with their dialogues and emotions. The reason she has been dodging him all summer is because she does not want to lead him on as she has a fantasy of doing the naughty with his partners. She does not know that Mike has one rule, never mix emotion with pleasure. Loved her character as she was direct with him about her fantasy.Mike and his business partners like to play. Wow! The play well together. Warning do not read in public, as will be squirming in your chair. The first sex scene is a scorcher, exciting and different. Kate's Crew has it all in the sexing department. It has M/F/M, M/M, M/M/M/M and M/M/M/F. Even though I loved how the sex scenes start off with just a few characters but then lead to more joining in as they are hot but felt they were a tad long for a short novella. I would of liked them cut back a little and had more of Kate and Mike. I will admit had to read a few times to get what the heck they were doing with so many characters. Fell in love with all the business partners and look forward to reading the rest of The Powertools series.Originally posted at Wickedly Delicious Book Blog
label: positive

text: Like many reviewers, we negotiated a lower rate for our room on Priceline, so we were very happy with the value we received. Like many upscale hotels, though, everything costs more. Internet is not included, parking is $45 per night (although you do get in/out privileges), and room service is extremely expensive. We never expect room service to be cheap but were quite surprised when our breakfast for 3 people was $125! My son was also disappointed that they don't have a swimming pool. The hotel is undergoing some renovations in the lobby, so it took away slightly from the overall beauty of the entrance, but it is still a very impressive hotel. The staff has been trained to provide the highest level of service, and we felt that they were oustanding throughout our stay. The location is close to the Metro and within walking distance of the White House. It's not as close as it looks, though, so if you're able to secure tickets to visit the White House, make sure you leave enough time to get there, or consider taking a taxi. There are many dining options within a few blocks of the hotel and the National Geographic Museum is a block over. Also, the Old Towne Trolley tour stops right in front of the hotel and is a great option for a city overview or even as transportation (although not a quick way) to get to the monuments, Smithsonian museums, and Arlington. The rooms aren't huge, but we never felt crowded (2 adults, 1 child) with a king bed and rollaway for our son, and we thought the beds were very comfortable. We would definitely consider staying here again.
label: positive

text:
一人プレイ好きにはオススメできない
３０分弱で一人プレイ用のチュートリアルを終え、さぁ次はキャンペーン（ストーリー）モードかと思いきや PS Plus の契約を要求する画面が出てきて金を払わないと先に進めない。 私は単純に広大な宇宙で自由に飛行し、ドッグファイトがしたいだけなのに。他の実在プレーヤーとやり取りしたいわけじゃない。オフラインだけでプレイしたい。私と同じ考えの人はこのゲームに６０００円も払う価値はない。 ここ（.co.jp）での評価は全体的に高いが、マルチプレーヤーばかりなのだろうか。北米（.com）の方では「オンラインじゃないとプレイできない」や「完全にマルチプレイ向き」、「マップや機体の数が少ない」という評価があって、私のようなシングルプレーヤーには不評のようだ。 PS VRの機能をフルに活かした没入感が素晴らしいだけに、キャンペーンモードや個性の違うAI（CPU）との対戦など、一人プレイ用の要素が無いのがあまりに勿体無い。購入を検討されている方は、そのへんを考慮しておかないと購入後に私のようにがっかりすることだろう。
label: negative

text: When I first started smoking cigars, I was hooked on Davidoff. I soon realized that $16 per cigar was just not gonna cut it, so I found another brand that I absolutely love. I came across this tiny little gem while walking to our Gondola ride and jsut had to stop in. Glad I did b/c they have an amazing selection of cigars, the customer service was just flat out awesome and the prices (despite what most people were writing on Yelp) were very reasonable. Again, I get my cigars at (they are gonna owe me a case for all the plugs I've given) famous-smoke.com and this store matched those prices within a dollar here or dollar there. They also have a small kiosk inside the casino at the Palazzo that is open really late. Again, the customer service was second to none. The gentlemen cut my cigar for me, handed me a pack of matches, pulled one out and lit the cigar for me. He could have just handed me the book of matches but he did me a solid and it's the little things that mean the most, ya know?? \n\nAwesome service, great prices and a wide selection of premium cigars make this a must for all levels of cigar smokers.
label: positive

text:
I debated going with 3 stars, but settled on two since 3 is supposed to mean "A-OK". First, the good things:
1) great homemade rootbeer and rootbeer floats, with 25 cent refills
2) Set up to handle large group events
3) Free/discounted meal on your birthday.
4) The smell of the pecan smokers is amazing.
5) The staff was very friendly

Unfortunately, the food is not so great. We were 2 couples, both of whom are serious BBQ lovers. I cure my own ham and bacon, make my own sausages, and smoke not only meats but also cheeses and other items. And since Seattle isn't exactly a BBQ mecca, we make a point of trying as much BBQ as possible on our yearly visits to Phoenix. We've found several great places here, but Joe's won't warrant a return visit.

Bruce and I each had the sampler plate, my wife Kim had the two item plate with turkey and pulled pork, and Steph had the two item plate with chicken and the jalapeno sausage. For side dishes we had beans, cheesy potatoes, and mac-n-cheese.
- brisket, pork and ribs were all overcooked and slightly dry.
- the sausage was OK, but nothing to write home about
- the chicken was the best of the meats, moist and tasty, but not particularly smoky
- the side dishes were mediocre, and most went unfinished. Of them, the corn (plain kernel corn) was OK, and the beans were pretty good.
- the rootbeer cake was dry and unmemorable, perhaps because the slices are precut and sitting out in the dry air on the cafeteria style serving line.

So if you are in Mesa/Gilbert and looking for quick BBQ, you can get a decent sized serving at a fair price here, but you'll be unlikely to be wowed by the food. If you really love BBQ, consider hopping back in the car and driving to Bobby Q, Texas BBQ House, or even Rudy's, all of whom do an amazing job of delivering fresh, moist meats with a great smoke flavor.
label: negative

text: My girlfriend and I stayed over valentines day for three nights. The first two nights we stayed in a deluxe room over looking the road. The room was nice a little small. The bathroom drain did not work and when we told the front desk nothing was done to fix the problem. The bed's are ok. But not what I have come to expect from a Hilton property. The 3rd night we had a regular room why they moved us is still anyone guess. The regular room was the smallest room I have ever stayed in in my life. It had one small window that faced a brick wall, and did not have any windows in the bathroom which would have been ok, but the fan did not work so if someone was showing it was really muggy in the entire room. Drain also did not work in this room A/C did not work in either room. The restaurant was decent, my girlfriend really liked her pasta, but my steak was nothing but fat. The Bar area was very nice. Staff was very kind even though they over looked all our issues with the drain and A/C. Also location was nice in relation to grand central. Currently working at two hotels one high end and one family friendly and being a active travel blogger with travel and leisure magazine. I have come to know what to expect and all sadly to say this property was lacking a little. I would stay again but not at the price I paid.

text: The hotel is in a great location and there is parking across the street on 41st street. The rooms was very large and the staff was very friendly. Our big disappointment was a 4:00 am fire alarm scare. NYC was already on high alert and it was scary. We called the desk and no one would answer. We along with many others went in the hallway and were getting ready to climb down the 32 flights. I called the phone in the hall for the 4th time and the desk clerk instructed us to go back to our rooms until they could locate the source of the alarm. The alarm went off two more times and the hotel announced for everyone to stay in rooms. We did not feel comfortable with the hotel's slow response time and lack of the source. We decided to get dressed and go wait outside the building. As we were about to leave an announcement came on to tell us that emergency was over and it was safe. I will tell you this-as soon as the first alarm went off-we saw firetrucks out side the building. Love and much respect to the firefighters of NYC. We felt the fire director did not take control of the situation fast enough and was glad to be checking out that day.
label: positive

It is very difficult to put down and I completed it within a week of starting it. The action is very well described and the strategy used by the Russians is certainly creative. It combines elements of land, sea and air. I have heard that this may become its own series. If so, I would likely read every one.

text: Открывала пластиковую дебетовую карту по акции Вернем 1000 рублей назад . Еще при оформлении в чате уточнила условия акции, а именно входит ли в Транзакции, засчитываемые в акции, оплата ЖКХ, т.к. в условиях нет МСС кодов, и значение фразы физические точки ТСП . На это мне был дан ответ, что оплата ЖКХ из приложения МТС однозначно засчитывается, а участие оплаты с сайта поставщика можно проверить после проводки операции. 16.12.2022 совершила оплату ЖКХ с сайта . и на следующий день узнала в чате, попала ли операция в акцию. Ответ был данная операция попадает в акцию . Соответственно, я не стала совершать больше никаких действий для участия акции (в тот момент для оплат были карты с бОльшим кэшбэком). Итого 2 раза в чатах мне однозначно подтвердили участие в акции оплат, совершенных ОНЛАЙН. Прошло 30 дней, в течение которых по условиям акции должна быть возвращена 1000 рублей. 1000 не выплачена. Обращаюсь в чат и получаю ответ ...К сожалению, онлайн платежи не участвуют в акции (( ...У Вас не были выполнены условия по акции, поэтому вознаграждение не поступает (( . Вместе со сроком выплаты истекли и 30 дней на совершение операций в рамках акции. Занавес.

text:
Уютный отель. Всё очень понравилось. 
Отдыхали с 30.06. по 03.07.2023
Обширная уютная территория, по которой разгуливают пятнистые олени. Домиков довольно-таки много, но никто никому не мешает. Недалеко от номера есть необустроеный песчанный пляжик. 
Домики есть новые и старенькие. 
Мы отдыхали в домике "три медведя" из числа старого номерного фонда. В целом всё понравилось. В домике микроволновая печь, холодильник, раковина, комплект посуды. Три спальни, гостинная и три санузла, что очень удобно для большой компании. Всё скомпановано на одном этаже, что очень удобно для посетителей с маленькими детьми. Рядом с каждым домиком мангал и стол со скамейками
В стоимость были включены завтраки и обеды по системе "шведский стол".Выбор не шибко большой, но безумно вкусно и сытно! 
Из минусов можно добавить следующее: слабый контроль за состоянием строений и оборудования (сгнившие доски на полу веранды, столик со скамейками на улице тоже потрепанного вида, немного разломаны фонари, но функционируют) 
От домика есть тропинка к воде. Вход в воду заросший, в воде останки разрушенного пирса. Интерьер довольно-таки тёмный, но всё равно уютно. 
По итогу могу сказать, что несмотря на указанные минусы, мы обязательно сюда вернёмся ещё раз!!! 
Очень надеюсь, что к этому времени вопрос с подходом к воде / пирсом будет решён.
label: positive

text:
Quel panier de crabes !
Il est vrai que ce livre vous offre une forme romanesque d'un drame familiale. J'ai découvert un milieu si loin du commun des mortels et, franchement, ne donne aucune envie d'en faire partie. N’étant absolument pas un fan du "Taulier" j'ai néanmoins chercher à comprendre pourquoi cet homme, apparemment généreux a décidé ou contraint de générer cette situation. Merci beaucoup pour cette enquête fouillée et richement documentée ainsi que pour cette narration palpitante.

text:
I was offered a free upgrade to a 2-room suite. The clerk actually said, "if you are a light sleeper, you might not like this room, it's near the elevator," but since I'm a solid sleeper, who also travels with a white noise machine, I figured it would be no problem. Oh my goodness, was that ever a horrible mistake. I barely slept that night. The thrumming, clanking, machinery noises switched on and off irregularly all night. Every time I got used to them, the pattern changed. The white noise machine was no help since the vibrations went right through the floors and wall, it wasn't just a noise you could block out. I finally got to sleep very late, then was startled awake at 3 am. I thought about getting up, repacking everything and moving rooms, but it was already so late and I had a big presentation the next day! It was easily the worst night of sleep I have had in a hotel since I stayed in an un-air- conditioned Howard Johnson's in 1992. The next day when I went to switch rooms they didn't seem surprised at all. . . I don't know who could sleep in those suite rooms. A homeless person accustomed to sleeping under a noisy bridge? Someone taking Ambien who is thus completely drugged out of their mind? Someone who drank about 40 martinis and then passed out? If none of these descriptors apply to you, then avoid those suites.
The regular room I switched to was fine, no complaints. Relief! They should convert the elevator-shaft suites into broom closets.
label: negative

text: We needed a place to stay on a below 60 night budget,which is nearly impossible and not have a dirty buggy room. We have stayed in the area many times and have actually passed by this hotel just because of the way and location it is in. However on this trip we needed something. We showed up at about 6pm to check in..which is thru a window. We asked to see the room before paying,which we were told they don't normaly do that,but I am persistant and believe before I give out money for a week I want to see what I'm getting. They agreed,I was totally suprised,it is dated,swag lighting,small tv with limited channels,but the room was clean,the carpet didn't look to old and was clean. The bathroom was also dated but clean,no mold on the curtain,or around the tub. The housekeepers for the dated building they have to deal with,I believe do a very good job. However bring your shampoo,body soap,hairdryer,alarm clock because other than a small round of soap the amenitys are sparse. I also bring these things just because no hotel ever gives you enough shampoo or bath soap and as far as a alarm every cell phone has one. The Beds are comfortable,there is a fridge with a small freezer part that keeps things nicely chilled,the only micro is located in the laundry/vending/ice area. Nights are quite and there is Mcdonalds right next door with a Dennys withing walking distance. The muni is right outside the parking lot. My overveiw of this hotel is, It isn't a Marriot but it also isn't a roach motel..for 53 a night you can get a clean room and a good nights sleep with the convience of being close to public transportation along with just about anything else you need. The downside the wifii you have to pay for, I paid for a month for 9.95 which was cheaper than by day or week..go figure, however you can use it anywhere there is a wifii hotspot,and the inroom phones need to be relined bad reception. I recommend this hotel for working or traveling people but as far as kids there isn't anything for them to do unless you take them offsite..Happy hoteling and good luck with your travels..hope this helps!
label: neutral

text:
Stayed 3 nights in October 2007 with wife and two young children. Room was clean and well maintained, but the Art Deco accents couldn't hide the fact that this is a rather plain building.
Kitchenette was well supplied with plates, cutlery, glasses and utensils, and was very functional. The table in the sitting/dining area, however, was too small; a coffee table rather than a dining table. Beds were very comfortable. As noted elsewhere, shower only (a strange decision, since it's a huge shower stall and could easily have fitted a bath). Staff were friendly and professional, but we had limited contact; no special requests made.
Location is excellent: close to restaurants and the Metro, but also very quiet. Good shopping nearby as well; check out the Firehook Bakery at Dupont Circle.
For the price, a good buy, but I wouldn't make it my automatic choice for a return visit. My benchmark for this kind of place is the Hotel Beacon in New York, and this lacks the space, comfort and quirky charm of that hotel.
label: positive

Executive Summary:Clean, comfortable, free wifi, though 'dated' furnishings... if you care about that kind of malarkey...

I quite enjoyed my 5 nights at the Delta Kitchener... but I think my standards of what a good hotel is are skewed a bit by years of backpacking and traveling on a shoestring budget.

To wit: I'm perplexed by comments in other reviews along the lines of "the bathroom was clean, but the room hadn't been updated in years.... though it too was clean and the bed comfortable." In my mind, a clean and comfortable bed and bathroom should be the primary feature being graded in hotel reviews... I don't really care if the furnishings looked 'tired'; I'm there to sleep, not learn new cutting edge design techniques.

Anyway - in addition to fulfilling the basic bed-and-cleanliness needs of a hotel-goer, there was also free wifi and the room I had was pretty big. All this for a very reasonable price (though I did get a group rate, so there is that...). That's four stars every day of the week in my book!

text:
Not bad for the price.
Super cute sandals, but they aren’t EXACTLY as the picture shown. The picture shows the color of the straps to be colored on both sides (meaning also the side against your skin). It is tan on the inside and the color you chose on the outside. Which isn’t a big deal...but if you want them to be exactly like the picture - they’re not. I am usually between an 8.5 - 9. Sandals and sneakers 8.5 and heels 9. So I originally went with the 8.5. They were too tight felt like I was going to rip the straps from the sole putting them on and they hurt just in a still position. Felt very tight and constricted. I sent them back...waited for a refund (since they don’t exchange) and ordered a 9. I feel they are cheaply made (but isn’t everything these days)... but for the price - I love the way they look and the 9’s fit much better. The sole is VERY thin. I thought I was going to feel every rock, pebble, and leaf through them, but they aren’t bad at all. Note: If your feet sweat a lot they definitely slip.

Stay at the Standard if you're looking for an LA Scene type place. The hotel feels pretentious from the get go. $30/day valet parking, beautiful lounge area no one actual uses, beautiful pool area that you better have a smoking body to compare with.

We heard alot about the poolside parties but it wasn't our kind of thing, so we gave it a miss. the problem is, if you want a drink by the pool after 7, you have to get fully dressed up and look the part.
breakfast not included and a simple breakfast for 2 at the restaurant came to about $40 before tips.
The location is also not great if you are exploring LA. For the price, find somewhere a little closer to Earth.
All in all, it looks really nice, but it wasn't our type of "scene". We would have preferred a place with a genuine and relaxed vibe.

text: This is the worst place to stay, if I could give it a "0" star rating I would. When booking this hotel it showed as a three and a half star (not true) Arrived for a late check in at 10:45pm. The room (#228) was very outdated and it had been painted to look updated with bright blue paint. The furniture was chipped, and the bathroom sink did not fit properly onto the vanity. The power strips under the TV were strung together by electrical cords. There was something disgusting on the carpet between the beds, told the kids to keep their shoes on. The restaurant/bar service door was below our single paned window and each time they would open the security screen door it would rattle our window. The WORST PART was awakening on Saturday morning at 6:00am to a contractor wearing crocs on a ladder outside our window sawing/grinding a metal structure. Smoke was coming in our room through the unsealed window. I called the reception desk to report this loud noise and smoke, she said she thought she smelled something too and would investigate...nothing was done. When I called for more towels (room only had 2) at 6:40am, no mention of a resolution. The guy was still sawing outside the window. When the towels were delivered at 7:10am. I inquired with Michele who was told of the problem from the off going night receptionist, but had no resolution. Said she was told by the guy that by city ordinance that he could start work at 6:00am. I showed her the smoke in the room and she said she would see what could be done...I told her we were leaving. Upon checking out at the front desk (7:40am), she gave me a photo copied coupon for 20.00 of my next stay....like I would want to go back there. We drove to the side that our room was located at to see smoke stains going up the wall outside our room window. DO NOT WASTE YOUR MONEY....

text:
I love the decor!

Like fellow Yelper Bao H. pointed out, this place caters to us ladies. My girlfriends and I went on a Friday night and were welcomed with the option to either be seated at a table or hang out by the bar. We opted for the bar as the place was not crowded and the tables were far apart. The bar itself is not very big and unfortunately there weren't any stools available to us, but we did get drink service pretty fast. Being a champagne lounge, the selection is quite extensive (and expensive), but they do also have beers and a full bar for one's other liquor needs. We didn't get to sample any of their snacks they offer, but I did see fried pickles, holla!

The attire was a bit more dressy and almost all the guys we encountered had on a jacket, one, might I add, had a purple velvet jacket on...nice. All the ladies were wearing heels and the majority had dresses on. The crowd that night consisted of 30+ somethings and mainly women.

Narcisse is located on the second floor so when its a little warmer out, the patio would be fund to hangout on to people watch. It does have a few heaters, but my friends still were not up for the winter challenge, bummer, but I guess its just another excuse to come back.

text: Хочу написать о работе сервиса Яндекс такси. Мало того, что там работают хамоватые водители, у них еще и дурацкая система оплаты, когда даже невыполненный заказ оплачивается. Причем деньги на счет не возвращаются. Рассказываю ситуацию: вызвала такси, чтоб поехать на вокзал. Таксист приехал в другой двор, так показывало приложение, а мне пришло сообщение, что меня одидает такси. Я позвонила водителю, чтоб сказать, что я его по прежнему жду, но по другому адресу, он не взял трубку. Я пошла его искать по дворам, но не нашла. На мое сообщение в приложение он ответил, что у него «моросит» навигатор. Я просила приехать по адресу, безрезультатно. Так как я спешила на вокзал и уже опаздывала, я вызвала другую машину, а ему написала, что не нуждаюсь в его услугах. Но у меня списались деньги, как будто я села в машину и поехала! Это возмутительно! То есть мало того, что я испытала стресс, я еще и заплатила за него!!! Хотя меня в службе поддержки уверяли, что вернут списанную сумму, этого не произошло. А я не один раз слышала, что водители в Яндекс такси назначаются на вызов оператором или автоматически, уж не знаю, и если они не хотят выполнять этот вызвов, то они где то поблизости от клиента останавливаются, клиент начинает звонить, а водитель не берпт трубку! Клиент теряет терпение, а таксисит типа начал поездку и снимают деньги с карты! Вот такая система в этом Яндекс такси. Не буду больше пользоваться услугами этого сервиса. Есть компании, где снимают дерьги только после поездки, и это правильно!!!

text:
It was a madhouse in there today with the grand opening. I opted out of the buy 1 get 1 coffee because 1) I am a tea drinker and 2) I was not with anyone who could try the second one. There was no way I was going to drink 2 coffees!

Nevertheless, I got there after 10 but still acquired a $5 gift card for being in the first 500 customers. The place was insanely crowded with people in suits - apparently there was some lawyer event outside and even some guys wearing cool pants dancing and hitting drums.

I ordered the vegetarian banh mi which included tofu and yam. I had no idea how to get in line originally until I asked, and then when my number was called I had no idea where to pick up...and finally figured it out. Oddly, I had completely forgotten that I have been to Lee's in Houston with my brother a few times but it was so long ago that I never made the connection when Lee's opened in Chinatown - I never went to that location and I thought it was only in California.

I think next time I will use my gift card for boba (avocado shake sounds pretty good right now!) - but my sandwich was unremarkable. I ate it while perusing fresh52 which led me to buy feta batard from Bon Breads :) The tofu (fried) and yam were shredded so that they appeared like potato sticks. The carrot and daikon cuts were much bigger. I was disappointed, because at Pho Thanh Huong I get the steamed tofu which is sizeable, clearly healthier, and more appealing to eat.

I do think it is cool that this joint opened in Henderson. For Henderson banh mi, I recommend Lemongrass Cafe. For central, PTH. I still need to try Dakao. Yet it is still nice to know I can get boba nearby, so I will be back!

text:
Pros:
- Highly professional, cheerful staff.
- Central location, close to Magnificent Mile, Lake Shore Drive, Navy Pier.
- Rooms are large, including a living room.
- Bed is very comfortable.
- Breakfast includes delicious omelets, freshly made to order.
- Complimentary snacks (pretty generous and tasty) every evening in the lobby.
- Impressive atrium, with super-fast glass elevators.
- Nice pool (although pretty small)
Cons (The basics):
- Bedroom walls could do with much better sound proofing. You may well get woken by people talking in a neighboring room. Confirmed in two different rooms.
- Bedroom windows could also do with better sound proofing. Lots of car horn sounds and even the growl of their engines. Confirmed in two different rooms.
- Black out curtains are difficult to close in such a way that no light comes in.
Cons (Additional observations):
- Tiny kitchen area is practical, but not even spoons are provided (e.g. for coffee/tea).
- Shampoo and conditioner provided, but difficult to open, especially with wet hands. Also no easy place to store them once opened around the bath tub.
- Towel rack is placed far away from the bath tub, so don’t forget to prepare your towel BEFORE you get in the shower/bath.
- Some general wear and tear is visible, and rooms could do with a good all round dusting.
- Pool area could do with a few deck chairs!
All in all, a good hotel, but I have stayed in much better hotels (for less money) in central Chicago).

text: История знакомства с этим прекрасным банком началась с 10.11.2022. Я пришел в отделение банка по адресу г. Москва, Гусятников переулок 13 3, с просьбой открыть счет и совершить перевод на свой счет в Тайланд. На мою просьбу одна из сотрудниц банка в данном отделение мне ответила Вы не видите, я устала вообще то, не загружайте меня, приходите завтра . На минуточку, время было 16 30 примерно, в этой ситуации мне помогла ее Коллега, сидящая рядом с ней. Людей тогда не было, я был единственный клиент находящийся в отделении, и меня заставляли ждать, пытались перенести на следующий день. И когда они открыли два счета (долларовый, рублевый) время уже было 18 00 и конвертация у них была не доступна!!! И мне действительно пришлось ждать следующий день! Перед тем как отправить перевод я подгрузил в приложении банка (в личном кабинете) подтверждающие документы о происхождении средств. два перевода которые я совершал через приложение доходили четко, на следующий день. Но Когда я пришел в банк повторно, а именно 17.11.2022, я отправил еще один перевод, банк на протяжении 24х часов держал мой платеж на обработке , хотя предыдущие два в течении 5-6 часов уходили в статус на исполнении . Я пришел в отделение банка на следующий день и задал вопрос, мне в эту же секунду прилетел запрос 115-ФЗ. То есть, если бы я этого не сделал - мои деньги бы висели в воздухе пока я сам бы не пришел и не спросил почему платеж висит в обработке? Мне сказали, описать полностью, куда уходят Деньги, цель их использования и так далее, хотя в запросе было написано ПРОИСХОЖДЕНИЕ СРЕДСТВ. я сразу же, не ждав ни секунды времени поехал Собирать документы, подтверждающие средства (Собрал порядка 25 документов, составил письмо на несколько листов А4 с полным Пояснением каждого документа И каждого действия). И действительно, платеж сразу ушел на исполнение и в понедельник (сегодня) был зачислен на карту Банкгок банка. я приехал сегодня в банк, чтоб отправить еще один перевод себе в Тайланд. меня позвала к себе сразу управляющая данного отделения У-НА ИРИНА А. и сказала вас к телефону, с вами хочет переговорить руководитель отдела Комплаенс - Максим. я взял трубку, со мной начали разговаривать, будто я попал в 90ые, процитирую - ты если обижен на нас, закрывай счет и переводи свои деньги в другую кредитную организацию - кто ты такой, что бы я из за тебя мог потерять банка корреспондента? - кто там слева от тебя диктует тебе что отвечать? Тебя за ручку водят? - если я щас официально скину бумажку с отказом и это увидят все банки если что, подумай хорошенько я если честно даже запинался когда слышал все эти фразы, в банке сидели помимо сотрудников еще клиенты и я держал эмоции при себе. А что самое интересное, я запросил официальный отказ моего Перевода. что сделала Ирина А. с Максимом? правильно, заблокировали мне личный кабинет в приложении и никакого отказа ни на почту, ни в приложение не пришло. Ирина А. меня настоятельно просила закрыть счет в банке, обещали в течение 10 минут официальный отказ от банка . . Мой совет тем, кто собирается пользоваться услугами данного банка - езжайте сразу в другой и не тратьте свое время. После такого отношения, мне кажется, что скоро они начнуть бить своих клиентов Которые задают неуместные для них вопросы. хотелось бы, чтобы этот вопрос проработали на высшем уровне и сделали правильные действия в пользу клиентов, готов возобновить с вами сотрудничество как клиент с банком при официальном извинении со стороны сотрудника Комплаенса.
label: negative

text: I stayed at the Grand Hyatt San Francisco for a trip to see family and friends. Although I've visited San Francisco many times for business and leisure, this is the first chance I had to stay at the Grand Hyatt. I picked it for several reasons - location, desire for Hyatt points, a reasonable rate for a downtown SF hotel, and the ability to use Amex points for 2 of the 5 night stay. The rooms were recently renovated and the furnishings were fabulous and much to my taste. The customer service of everyone ranging from front desk to housekeeping staff was exceptional. One minor drawback was that the lobby was much smaller than usual due to renovation so it was packed all the time. But again, the staff made up for it by their friendly demeanor. The location couldn't be beat. I had decided not to rent a car because of the cost and I didn't regret my decision for an instant. I walked everywhere, took BART to Oakland to see friends, and took the cable car from Ghirardelli Square. I had a few minor issues that were resolved at checkout and through a follow-up contact to my survey responses. Very impressive!!! I look forward to staying there again on future trips to the Bay area.
label: positive

text: Si nous en savions déjà beaucoup sur Nahik, notamment grâce aux derniers tomes, il nous restait encore un secret à découvrir : les origines mêmes du texte. Giroud remonte ici beaucoup plus loin dans le temps, en l'an 652, à Médine. J'éviterai de trop en dire, mais sachez que cet ultime tome tient toutes ses promesses, avec un scénario une fois de plus passionnant de bout en bout. De plus, ce dixième tome est l'un des plus beaux graphiquement de la série, ce qui n'est pas pour déplaire ! Au final, "Le Décalogue" est une grande série qu'il est toutefois difficile d'appréhender au début. Les premiers tomes, s'ils restent dans l'ensemble très réussis, donnent peu d'indications sur les intentions réelles de Giroud. C'est vraiment à partir du tome 7 que la série se met à enchaîner les révélations et où le récit prend une nouvelle dimension. Une fois le dixième tome terminé, on peut s'amuser à relire les tomes dans l'ordre décroissant, et là tout le génie de Giroud apparaît dans toute sa splendeur. Tout s'enchaîne remarquablement, pleins d'éléments qui paraissaient nébuleux à la première lecture, prennent alors tout leur sens, c'est tout simplement vertigineux. Les thématiques de la série (les rapports qui ont toujours lié le sacré aux êtres humains, à quel point le divin a toujours déchaîné les passions humaines, pour le meilleur et pour le pire, et les dangers immenses encourus par l'Humanité lorsqu'il lui prend l'envie de manipuler ces croyances afin de servir ses propres intérêts, qu'ils soient politiques ou idéologiques) n'en prennent que plus de force encore. Si les scénarios de la série sont incroyables, il est malheureusement impossible d'en dire autant sur son aspect visuel. La multiplicité des dessinateurs ne sert pas vraiment la série, le nombre de tomes bien dessinés se révélant être une minorité. Heureusement, la série se finit sur deux tomes vraiment très jolis, achevant "Le Décalogue" sur une bonne note, et rendant justice à la richesse hors normes d'une oeuvre à découvrir pour tous les amateurs de bandes dessinées.
label: positive

text:
Wow for their traditional Chinese food!!

Went with our Chinese collegues as part of farewell lunch. Wish we discovered the place earlier. Never had such a good traditional food before, at least not in Chandler. They specialized in Canton and Szechuan (Sichuan) food.

We ordered 7 dishes, started with my personal favorites in ranking below
1. Claypot fillet fish (Szechuan Style), 
2. Claypot Ma Po Tofu with seafood, 
3. Szechuan Style Spicy Chicken Wings, 
4. Szechuan Style Sizzling Sliced Pork, 
5. Fried Kailan (chinese native vegetable), 
6. Eggplant w/ Spicy Garlic Sauce
7. Shan Dong Marinated Pork

I would say you would never go wrong with claypot type and if you ordered on based on the pictures displayed on the walls. I li

Wish the spicy food were spicier, since many of us are able to take level 4 spicyness material.

The place is small and I have not seen folks ordering American Chinese food there, so beware if you're looking for orange chicken, etc. Restaurant.com coupon no longer accepted - but the coupon always made the owners unhappy, not sure what their grouses are with this coupon company. Service is mediocore as it is family oriented with limited resource, the aunty is a serious person with lack of smile similar to the one you experienced in any San Francisco good old pigeon hole Chinatown restaurant. 

In summary, authentic food lovers that does not care about service should go to this little gem
label: neutral

text: Stayed here for a week on business. Conveniently located, happy & helpful staff, nice workout room, & the restaurant on site had good food (I was surprised to find a huge organic salad on the menu). The major downfall of this hotel is it's age & need for renovation. My room had a damp smell, old dingy furniture (I would need to put a blanket on the couch before I sat on it), & gross calcium buildup on the shower head. I'm a Hilton diamond member & am overall comfortable in Hilton's but this one needs some TLC. The internet was a bit slow but this is the norm for hotels in general. It wasn't bad enough for me to leave & if I was having trouble finding other hotels I would stay here again but it won't be my first choice.

text: I stayed in their Junior suite which includes a King bed in the bedroom and a queen pull out in the living room area. I really liked that the bedroom and living room were completely separated. Oh and there were two full bathrooms which is extremely essential for girls. The bathroom connected to the bedroom had two separate sinks, a separate door for the toilet, a shower, and a jacuzzi. The bathroom in the living area had the shower and toilet together. There was also a table, kitchen with stove and large refrigerator. there was a balcony to go outside as well. There were two flatscreens and even a DVD player for you to play your own movies. There are two closets in the living room and 4 drawers. Definitely ample space. \nI liked that the Signature is private, completely closed off from any other guests. There is a gate to enter for guests only. This is perfect for families or people who don't want a casino in their hotel. There is a 10 min indoor walkway from the Signature to the MGM which is extremely convenient if you don't want to take your car out of the valet or if you just want to grab a bite at the MGM. \nThe hotel isn't on Las Vegas Blvd, but its very close to the strip still to do all your things on the strip. I would definitely stay here again for the cleanliness and peaceful atmosphere of the hotel. It felt like I was in a condo more than just a regular room, which I definitely prefer.
label: neutral

text:
Went here with some friends while my husband and I were having our couple's shower in Vegas prior to our wedding. His best man raved about the restaurant, so we decided to give it a go.

We made a reservation for the first seating, but they weren't quite ready for us when we got there, so we sat in the bar area and ordered a couple of drinks. I got a very good pino noir, though I can't recall where it was from.

When it was time to be seated, we were escorted to our table through a line of wait staff. Honestly, it was a bit uncomfortable walking through all those people. Once we got to our table, our server came over and gave us menus. Both the server and her assistant were pleasant enough, though I don't know I would go as far as saying there were "friendly."

We all ordered our starters and make courses, plus a couple of sides. I got the lobster bisque, which I wasn't all that impressed with. I had better lobster bisque on cruise ship. It was a bit salty and the way they presented it was a bit tacky, in my opinion.

When the entrees came, everything was fine. The steak was good, but I don't know that I would ever pay $50+ for it again. I asked for medium, and I got medium rare. Which was fine for me, but one of my friends had the same problem, and it kinda grossed her out. So she had to send it back. The server got the problem fixed very quickly, and it was perfect the second time around.

I did like that they came with some sauces. The Bearnaise was very good and my husband devoured the peppercorn sauces. The sides were all good, but not as big as we had anticipated. Our waiter said they should feed 3-4 people. However, when you have two 250+ pound guys with you, it was not enough.

The desserts were FANTASTIC. I had the creme brule, which was perfect. Soft and creamy, with a yummy hard shell on the top. I would order that again in a heart beat. And we all felt the deserts were very reasonably priced for what we received. Definitely big enough for 2 people to share.

Overall, 3 starts. Everything was good and probably would have gotten 4 stars, if not for the price of everything. When you pay that much for food, you expect to be wowed. And we just weren't. But no major complaints either.
label: negative

text:
Room - we had a recently partly refurbished room that had a really nice comfy bed and a large TV. The bathroom needed a good detail clean - some yucky stains on the bathroom wallpaper etc. Bath tub was great for a hot soak in winter. Room was big enough to lay our large bags out on the floor and had a walk in style closet with heaps of hanging space for winter coats. Heating in room was good - we didn't feel the cold once. Big flat screen TV was great. My main gripe was that there was no coffee/tea making facilities in the room. We requested a coffee maker and got one however we had to call room service everyday to get a coffee sachet and milk brought up to the room. Plus - house keeping would not service the mugs or coffee area as part of their house keeping so we had to just make do. For a hotel which I am sure must attract a lot of UN staff and business travelers as well as tourists like us - surely coffee/tea in room facilities is a basic MUST!?
Service - excellent. All staff we encountered we amazing. Room service was tasty and quick.
Location - $5 cab ride to all the great immediate touristy spots or do like we did - a 10/15 min walk to everywhere we wanted to go. We found it very friendly and very safe.
Value - we stayed over NYE (PEAK period) and it was by far the best price we could find in a hotel of decent standards. Very happy with the overall value.
Would stay here again - especially if hotel ups the cleanliness standards and supplies the basic coffee/tea facilities!
label: positive

仕事柄、靴の中が蒸れてしまうのが悩みでした。 通気性がよく、できれば破れにくいソックスを探していました。 このメンズ用の5本指ソックスを見つけ、レビュー内容がとてもよかったので試しに購入してみることにしました。 【素材が綿で通気性抜群なのが魅力的！】 素材は綿を使用していました。 質のいい綿を使用しているのか、通気性も吸収性もとてもよかったです。 弾力性もあり、長時間歩いても足の裏が痛くなりませんでした。 汗をたくさんかいているのに、全く嫌なにおいがしなくなったのはとてもうれしいです。 靴をぬがなくてはいけなくなった場合でも安心です。 水虫対策にもなるかとおもいます。 デザインもシンプルで、ブラックなので使い勝手もとてもいいです。 ビジネス以外にも使用しやすいかと思います。 10本セットなので洗い替えもばっちりで、値段も安いのでコスパも◎です♪ 【強度がしっかりしているのに驚きました】 ソックスの厚みはそこまで厚くない感じでするっと履くことが出来ました。 厚みがないので強度はあまりないのかな？と思っていましたがつま先が強化されていました。 穴が開きやすいつま先への配慮もあり、お気に入りのソックスになりましたよ。 これから使い続けて、どれほど強度があるのか試してみるのも楽しみです。 かかとにはつなぎ目もなく、足と靴の摩擦も感じにくかったです。 弾力性もあり、まるでオーダーしたソックスのような感覚がします（笑） 柔らかくて伸びも抜群でした。 ソックスは消耗品のため、だめになってしまったらまた購入したいと思います。 【プレゼントにもいいかも！】 バレンタインなどのちょっとしたプレゼントにもらうととても嬉しいと感じます。 とても仲のいい間柄であれば、なおさらいいですね！ すぐにダメになってしまうものなので、もらうと嬉しいものだと思います。 私は個人的にとてもいい買い物をしたと思ったので、父に父の日のプレゼントとしてあげました。 始めて5本指ソックスを履いたといっていましたが、気持ちよかったと喜んでくれましたよ！
label: positive

text: The Dakota hotel is a great place to stay in San Francisco! The location is perfect! It is only two blocks from Union Square and very close to all tourist destinations. I stayed in a dorm room, but it was quite spacious and even had a full bathroom. It was very clean, and I could tell well taken care of. The dorm had bunk beds, but it was still very comfortable and I slept quite well. The rooms also have large windows looking out to the big city views. The staff here are so accommodating! There was one in particular, i think his name was Raymond, who would always great me with a friendly smile and made sure to help me with any problems I had during my stay. So sweet and such a kind demeanor, I suggest anyone staying here go to him for advice and assistance with even the smallest of requests. The staff also plan nightly events to entertain you, my personal favorite being wine & cheese night in the lounge. They make it very easy for you to meet other guests and make friends with fellow travelers. You really feel at home here with the comfort they provide you. I will definitely be staying here again when I find my way back to San Francisco.
label: positive

text:
If you're looking for a Jersey Shore douche party featuring DJ Suck, then this is your joint. But that's just your typical day club atmosphere and not why I rated this pool so low.

First of all, this place is FILTHY. We walked in and the whole place smelled like urine and drunken desperation. We had a cabana and the little carpet inside was sticky under our feet. The daybed attached to our cabana was lined with towels but they were all stanky and full of questionable stains. Like, seriously? A $1500 cabana and the staff can't change the towels on the day bed? And I cannot convey enough how disgusting the pool was. The water was thick and soupy with random floating debris and hair floating everywhere. It looked like it hadn't been properly cleaned in a month. I stepped in up to my shins and it was at that point I decided that fully submerging in that sewer water would surely result in a staph infection or pregnancy. I got out and had long ass hair stuck to my foot. I was, and still am, totally grossed out.

The food we ordered was very good but the staff wasn't super attentive. Again, for a$1500 cabana with auto grat, the service should have been stellar. It was getting to the point where I wanted to put a little bell around my server's neck. 

Seriously. When I dress up, wait in line, deal with the cockbag doormen, and pay a million dollars for food and drinks, I expect a clean cabana, attentive service and pool water that isn't an eleven on a scale of 1 to Erin Brockovich.
label: negative

This film might have been more, as there was suitable budget for settings, actors and a decent story line. My wife and I both agreed that this was 'Muck' at the end, as the film ended on a painful embarrassing high! Better luck next time, hope Miss Graham sticks to the type of films that she belongs in like From Hell.

text:
Falsche Polung, Videosignal auf dem Roten Stecker. Funktion aber OK.
Das Kabel habe ich für einen LG OLED TV gekauft, welcher mittels 4 Pin Klinke auf S-Video Adaptiert werden kann. Beim Anschluss habe ich mich über ein Brummen gewundert, was aus den Lautsprechern kam und ebenso über ein fehlendes Bildsignal. Erst nachdem ich die alten Geräte (Nintendo, Playstation etc.) bewusst "falsch" angeschlossen habe, hat dieser Adapter funktioniert. Und zwar wird das Videosignal NICHT wie gewohnt über den gelben, sondern über den Roten Stecker übertragen und der Gelbe funktioniert als Audio Kanal. Warum der Hersteller nicht darauf hinweist, ist mir ein Rätsel. Ebenso könnte auch ein Produktionsfehler verantwortlich sein, allerdings kann man doch bei einem geringwertigen Artikel wie diesem Adapter eigentlich nicht viel schief gehen.
label: negative

text:
The Mandalay buffet has gone downhill since I first went here many years ago. It was once a grand seafood buffet with abundant alaskan crab. Now its just kinda sorry. The line for the crab is super long and everyone is waiting for the small stash of crab legs that the staff slowly (strategically) stocks.

The primerib was salty and tasted like one of those "cured" wrapped primeribs you get at the supermarket. The naan bread was more like pita bread, hard and crunchy. 

The only things worth getting here was the salmon, pizza, and watermelon. Unfortunately, thats not why I go to Vegas buffets. 

Good thing the entire buffet was comped or else I would have been more upset.
label: negative

It got the point that we went to the bell captain for information, which he gladly gave us. We seemed to get the same waiter every time we were in the bar, and he also seemed very put out when we wanted anything. It took an hour to get a toothbrush delivered to the room for one of our group whose luggage was delayed (had to call front desk three times). The amazing location made up for much of these issued, because we were only in the room for showering and sleeping.

text: Booked this hotel via travel zoo for the Easter long weekend. We went for the optional upgrade and were pleasantly surprised to get a suite on a high floor overlooking the water. In addition, we rec'd free wi-fi and free parking. This is a huge hotel with two large towers connected via a walkway. No need to eat at the pricey restaurants at the hotel as you are right by everything on the magnificent mile. We walked everywhere - Buckingham Fountain, House of Blues, The Purple Pig and of course to the shopping. Bed was very comfortable and room was kept relatively clean. Great closet space but very few drawers. Due to the size of the hotel the wait at the elevators was a tad bit long. We did try room service which was quick and good but very expensive. Would return if we can get a similar deal!

My girlfriend and I stayed here as a stop off on our backpacking trip around the world. Firstly I would not recommend this hotel to business people etc looking for a bargain. It is very basic with a TV and shared shower facilities.
The hotel is located in an undergoing regeneration project of downtown L.A, if you keep going east on 7th you will feel very unsafe so go west when you exit the hotel which brings you more into the financial areas of downtown L.A where lots of good bars can be found such as Caseys.
The staff were very friendly though and very helpful so full marks for them.
Again to get to the point.....only stay here if you are backpacking and on a budget.

text: Ужасное место. Уточню, их точка ещё есть ещё в Мэтр на циолковского. Эти ребята продали нам шкаф, со сроками все хорошо, уложились, а вот качество и обслуживание просто конченное и со стороны фабрики и со стороны продавца в мэтре. Шкаф собирал сам и я просто в ужасе, что в 2023 году мебель даже бюджетного класса далается в ручную, да ещё и криво косо... Везде где есть отверстия, имеются линии и грязь от карандаша! ДСП белого цвета и грязь была повсюду, в том числе и следы не понятно от чего, то-ли кровь мастера, то-ли ещё какие-то выделения. Отверстия со сколами! Ужас, одна доска вообще была разамечена неправильно. В комплект не положили гвоздей для того, чтобы прибить заднюю стенку. Нет заглушек на мебельные болты! Работа сделана халатно! При разговоре с заводом было море хамства, когда приехали в Мэтр, продавец вытащила какую то помойку с гвоздями и прочим мебельными мусором и сказала "набирайте сами", сами! короче хамство кругом. Продавцу главное продать, заводу пофиг на все. Если хотите геморроя, то вам именно в это место. Всем остальным НЕ ОБРАЩАЙТЕСЬ В ЭТОТ ШАРАЖ!!!
label: negative
